 deep tensions and complexities of collective life and the power disintegrative forces posed to social order. Rousseau believed that the ever precarious social order could only be achieved artificially, by manufacturing "sentiments of sociability," reshaping individuals to identify with common interests instead of their own selfish interests.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEnlightenmentxFrance. 0aEnlightenmentzFrance. 0aSiècle des lumièresxFrance. 4aPhilosophy : Critical Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791487433423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791487433/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles